Darrell Long (darrell@oak.cse.ucsc.edu) writes:

> details) of a low exponent attack on RSA.  SInce PGP using a small public
> exponent, is it vulnerable to this attack?

This was discussed here some time ago. If I remember correctly, the
conclusion was that the low exponent attack works only for pure RSA -
i.e., when the message is encrypted as-is. Since PGP uses random
padding before RSA-encrypting the message (which is short, randomly
generated, and different even for plaintexts with the same contents),
it is not vulnerable to this attack.

Regards,
Vesselin
